               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370814-name-1268" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370814-name-1268" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370814-name-1268" type="surname" value="CHAPMAN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370814-name-1268" type="given" value="ELIZABETH"></interp>ELIZABETH CHAPMAN</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the wife of James Chapman. I keep the Coach and Horses, at Stratford—I had a wooden bowl, with this property in it. On the 8th of August the prisoner came in and opened the till, and took the bowl out with the silver in it—I was not two yards from him—I nearly caught him—I cried out "Stop thief," and he was taken by Willis—I am positive he is the boy.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
